<h2>Pack contents</h2>

<h3>Pre-action documents</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Letter Before Claim - formal demand to send before issuing proceedings</li>
  <li>Information Sheet for Defendants - defendant guidance to enclose with the letter</li>
  <li>Reply Form - response form for the defendant</li>
  <li>Financial Statement Form - used if the defendant proposes a payment arrangement</li>
</ol>

<h3>Court claim documents</h3>
<ol start="5">
  <li>Official Form N1 (PDF) - populated with the core claim details</li>
  <li>Particulars of Claim - drafted summary of the rent, loss, and legal basis of the claim</li>
  <li>Schedule of Arrears - period-by-period breakdown of the debt</li>
  <li>Interest Calculation Sheet - daily-rate workings for section 69 County Courts Act 1984 interest</li>
  <li>Evidence Index - checklist for the documents you may need to exhibit</li>
</ol>

<h3>Guidance documents</h3>
<ol start="10">
  <li>Money Claim Filing Guide - practical steps for MCOL or paper issue</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Total documents: 10</strong> so the debt letter, claim, figures, and filing guidance sit in one file set.</p>

<h2>Before you issue the claim</h2>

<p><strong>Do not issue the N1 immediately.</strong> Work through these steps first:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Send the <strong>Letter Before Claim</strong> to the defendant by first class post or email</li>
  <li>Enclose the <strong>Information Sheet</strong>, <strong>Reply Form</strong>, and <strong>Financial Statement Form</strong></li>
  <li>Wait <strong>30 days</strong> for the defendant to respond or pay</li>
  <li>Keep proof that the letter and enclosures were sent</li>
</ol>

<p>If you do not follow the Pre-Action Protocol for Debt Claims, the court may:</p>
<ul>
  <li>strike out the claim;</li>
  <li>order costs against you; or</li>
  <li>limit the interest or costs you recover.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Usually move on to court only if:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>the defendant does not respond within 30 days;</li>
  <li>the defendant disputes the debt without a sustainable answer; or</li>
  <li>no reasonable payment plan can be agreed.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Filing steps after the 30-day response period</h2>
<ol>
  <li>File online via Money Claim Online (MCOL) if the claim is suitable for online issue, or send the printed claim by post</li>
  <li>Attach the particulars, arrears schedule, interest sheet, and evidence index in the same order each time</li>
  <li>Include proof that the Letter Before Claim was sent and the 30-day period was allowed to expire</li>
  <li>Pay the court fee and retain the claim reference with the pack</li>
</ol>

